relatedmaterial.head: Related Material at the New York University Archives
relatedmaterial.p: There are two interviews regarding the history department with professors Carl Prince and David Hicks in the Records of the NYU Public History Program Box 15, folders 6 and 7.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: This collection contains administrative records of the History Department. Materials include staff files, budget information, and correspondence.

bioghist.head: Historical/Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Department of History is located within the Faculty of Arts and Science at NYU. History has been taught at NYU since the University's founding in 1831, but it was not until 1893 that NYU formed academic departments, including one in history. Courses are offered to undergraduates and graduates.

Fax: (212) 995-4225

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: Institutional records of New York University are closed for a period of 20 years from the date of their creation (the date on which each document was written). Board of Trustees records are similarly closed for 35 years from the date of creation. The opening date for files spanning several years will be 20 years from the most recent date. Access will be given to material already 20 years old contained within a collection that is not yet open when such material can be isolated from the rest of the collection.

Materials related to personnel, faculty grievances, job searches and all files with information that falls under the University's Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) policy are permanently restricted.

custodhist.head: Provenance
custodhist.p: This collection was transferred to the University Archives from the History Department.
